    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-11-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="272"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/826.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 362.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 21, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Sir: * * * Some weeks ago the Legation advised Americans in the regions affected
                    by military operations in the provinces of <pb facs="0283" n="167"
                        xml:id="pg_167"/> Chihli, Shansi and Honan to send their families to places
                    of safety. Most of them have done so. Similar action was taken by many consuls
                    whose districts were affected by revolutionary risings.</p>
                <p>The increase of lawlessness and the reports of attacks upon foreigners seem to
                    call for a general removal of our citizens so far as possible to ports that are
                    accessible to naval vessels, and on the 18th instant therefore I issued a
                    circular of instruction to the consuls to that effect.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Calhoun.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
